main event: A civilian reported seeing a bright object streaking across the sky, resembling a shooting star, on 3 September 1965.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 1 second., The object was described as having a tail of brilliant light., The observation is consistent with many other unidentified flying object reports., No physical evidence or photographs were collected regarding this sighting., The official conclusion by the Air Force classifies it as a meteor.
sighted object: a bright object streaking across the sky
witness description: reported by a civilian along with family members
